The pragulous public transport (MHD) will introduce the chip into their ticketing system on Wednesday
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of the Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Pragous Transportation Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will be taken to the subway, trams and buses, which, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, it is accessible for about one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day coupon or 90-day coupon (the coupon will be valid from 1 January 2009) and have it recorded on their smart card at the information points and the offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located at the Metro Stations Muzeum, M. Stek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letěany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday on, there is also the possibility to purchase coupons via the Internet on the web pages of Dopravní podnik: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people benefited from the service during the morning.
Those who will begin to use the online store can permanently forget the windows in the metro stations, where they had to tread out impatience in long queues in order to get paper tickets.
In fact, they will purchase their coupons online and will be recorded on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"At these points of contact, there is a window available to passengers with trained staff, which will help those interested with the purchase via the internet and will also record the coupon they purchased on their cards," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Besides libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recall the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them at the Roztyly Metro Stations, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be ninety," Opatrný added.
An automatic controls the coupon instead of the driver
Autos that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just enter the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will register itself on the card.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital, but also around the city.
In the peri-urban trains and bus lines 300 to 499, which are mainly used by the inhabitants of the municipalities of the Bohème centrale to access the capital.
